3 MCMC

data <- list("y", "m", "p", "nc", "nq", "ns")

# parameters to be monitored:
parameters <- c('gamma', 's', 'ypred')

# model
model_text <- "
# Individual Search Orders
model{   
  # Data
  for (i in 1:ns){
    for (q in 1:nq){
      y[i,q] ~ dbern(ttb[t[i,q]])
      ypred[i,q] ~ dbern(ttb[t[i,q]])
    }
  }
  # One Reason Model, With Different Search Order Per Subject
  for (i in 1:ns){
    for (q in 1:nq){    
      # Add Cue Contributions To Mimic TTB Decision
      for (j in 1:nc){
        tmp1[i,q,j] <- (m[p[q,1],j]-m[p[q,2],j])*pow(2,s[i,j]-1)
      }
      # Find if Cue Favors First, Second, or Neither Stimulus
      tmp2[i,q] <- sum(tmp1[i,q,1:nc])
      tmp3[i,q] <- -1*step(-tmp2[i,q])+step(tmp2[i,q])
      t[i,q] <- tmp3[i,q]+2
    }
    # Cue Search Order From Ranking stmp
    s[i,1:nc] <- rank(stmp[i,1:nc])
    for (j in 1:nc){
      stmp[i,j] ~ dnorm(0,.001)
    }
  }
  # Choose TTB Decision With Probability Gamma, or Guess
  ttb[1] <- 1-gamma
  ttb[2] <- 0.5
  ttb[3] <- gamma
  # Prior
  gamma ~ dunif(0.5,1)
}
"
samples <- jags(data, parameters.to.save = parameters, 
                model.file = textConnection(model_text), 
                n.chains=4, n.iter=5000, n.burnin=2000, n.thin=1)

4.3 Search order

s <- samples$BUGSoutput$sims.matrix[,3:182]

# Matlab에 비해 많이 느리다. 
showorders <- 10 
for (ss in 1:20) {
  sv <- s[,seq(ss,180,by=20)] # this subject's validity order samples
  nsv <- dim(sv)[1]
  ut <- unique(sv) # unique validity order
  nut <- dim(ut)[1]
  
  cnt <- rep(0,nut)
  
  sv <- as.data.frame(sv)
  ut <- as.data.frame(ut)
  # message off
  # https://stackoverflow.com/questions/28311293/how-to-make-join-operations-in-dplyr-silent
  for (i in 1:nut) {cnt[i] <- nrow(suppressMessages(plyr::match_df(sv, ut[i,])))}
  ms <- order(cnt, decreasing = TRUE) # mass of unique validities
  # cnt[ms[1:10]] # cnt[ms[1:10]]/nsv = estimated mass 교재와 비교하여 너무 작다.
  print(paste("Subject ", ss))
  
  for (xx in 1:showorders) { # valitity value가 높은 순서대로 단서 번호를 재정렬.
    ut[xx,] <- order(as.matrix(ut[ms[xx],]), decreasing=TRUE)
  }
  tmp <- ut[1:showorders,]
  colnames(tmp) <- 1:9
  tmp %>% mutate(count = cnt[ms[1:showorders]]) %>% print()
}
